      "message": "I\u0027m a little fuzzy-headed still so I\u0027d like to wait until tomorrow to fully comment on this. But initial thoughts:\n* I don\u0027t think we need fActiveRenderCmdEncoder at all as the commandBuffer tracks that. We can reacquire it in onDraw() with the same parameters as in bindPipeline()\n* That said, it\u0027s possible for someone to inject something between bindPipeline() and onDraw() which, say, creates a blitCmdEncoder and discards the original renderCmdEncoder -- that could cause weird state issues.",
